url: "https://github.com/aditya89bh/meeting-memory-system"
abstract: >-
  A deterministic, local-first system that converts raw meeting transcripts into durable,
  queryable institutional memory. It extracts typed memory primitives (decisions,
  commitments, risks, questions, assumptions, open loops, facts), links them across
  meetings into an organizational graph, and mines them for deterministic organizational
  intelligence — exposed through a CLI, REST API, Python SDK, and web dashboard. It uses
  no LLM APIs, embeddings, or vector databases.
keywords:
  - meetings
  - transcripts
  - institutional-memory
  - knowledge-graph
  - organizational-intelligence
  - deterministic
